methods.call:
A function that would like to take a snapshot of data guarded by a retry loop with data consistency tests.

:param usePrev: (boolean) - Whether data from the previous cycle should be used (otherwise use this cycle)
:param beforeClockValue: (long) - The clock value that we captured before the function began; the function can use this
        value to bail out early if it notices something has gone wrong
:return: (boolean) true if the function was successful, false if it should be retried
